# Monorepo conventions

## Package boundaries

- `apps/patflow` and `apps/patstore` — routes and app-specific layout only
- `packages/modules` — feature UI and business logic (`patflow/` and `patstore/` subdirs)
- `packages/types` — TypeScript types (`@repo/types`)
- `packages/provider` — data hooks, contexts, auth (`@repo/provider`)
- `packages/ui` — reusable components (`@repo/ui`)

## Adding a feature

1. Types in `packages/types/src/{app}/`
2. UI/logic in `packages/modules/src/{app}/`
3. Thin route in `apps/{app}/app/(application)/.../page.tsx`:

```tsx
export { MyFeature as default } from "@repo/modules";
```

4. Export new module from `packages/modules/src/{app}/index.ts` and `packages/modules/src/index.ts` if needed

## Do not

- Put feature logic directly in app `page.tsx` files
- Duplicate types across packages
- Import from apps into packages (packages must not depend on apps)
- Expose `SASHIDO_MASTER_KEY` or master-key queries in client components

## Commands

```bash
npm run dev:patflow   # port 3002
npm run dev:patstore  # port 3001
npm run lint
```
